question: Based on the following hair salon review, what are the atypical aspects for a hair salon? context: Mary gives fabulous cuts -- I'd been going to her at the Saturn Club for years, so didn't hesitate about following her to Deluxe. This newly renovated space is nice and modern and in a convenient location (next to bicycle therapy). Mary also tries hard to accommodate your schedule.
Haven't tried any of the other stylists yet, but Mary's great! 
Haircuts are about $45.

preds: ["The hair salon has two vehicles for the tots to choose from as well as toys, children's songs and television cartoons.", '', 'The salon has live jazz on the weekends. Ciao also carries all sorts of quality hair products which they sell for good prices.', 'The salon has a new eyelash extension offer on Groupon.', 'The hair salon sells vintage dresses, new designer T shirts, and best of all - all kinds of amazing, one of a kind jewelry pieces and handmade hats and scarfs. They offers waxing, spray tanning, makeup, and bridal services.', '', 'The hair salon has drinks, snacks, free wifi, coloring books (for adults), beauty bar and much more.', '', 'The salon has an art gallery and a fashion part of the store.', 'The hair salon uses their anniversary party every year as a fundraiser for local causes.', "The hair salon's ads draw anthropomorphic coyotes in them and the owner helps a dog saving organization.", '']
labels: [['The salon is a community art space. There is always great local art for sale on the walls, the occasional yoga class where proceeds go to local community organizations, and beauty nights where you get to learn about and test products for free. The salon offers waxing, spray tanning, makeup, and bridal services.'], ['There is an ATM in the salon.'], ['The salon has free wifi.
